    "department": "Design",
    "description": "ABOUT POLYMARKET\n\nPolymarket is the world’s largest prediction market platform. We enable individuals to express views on real-world events by trading on outcomes across politics, economics, sports, culture, and current affairs. Built as a peer-to-peer marketplace with no centralized “house,” Polymarket aggregates diverse opinions into transparent, market-based probabilities that reflect collective expectations about the future.\n\nWe're growing fast – both in terms of volume ($21B traded in 2025) and adoption as an alternative news source. Our ambition is to become a ubiquitous beacon of truth in global media and we need your help adding fuel to the fire.\n\n\n\n\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nPolymarket is looking for an experienced Product Designer to join our NYC team. You must live and breathe product and be obsessed with understanding user behavior.\n\nThe ideal candidate will have a strong background in designing beautiful world-class consumer products, with a high bar for craft and a focus on creating deeply engaging, user-centric experiences. You will work directly with our Founder and company leadership to spearhead every step of the design process from idea to launch, ensuring that our products are not only functional but also delightful.\n\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL DO\n\n - Visual and interaction design. You’ll create visually stunning and highly interactive designs that resonate with our users. Your work should demonstrate a keen eye for detail and a deep appreciation for craft.\n\n - Lead design end-to-end. You’ll partner with cross-functional leads and take charge of design initiatives, crafting innovative solutions from scratch that meet both user needs and business goals.\n\n - Conduct user research. You’ll perform detailed user research to inform design decisions and contribute to the overall strategy and direction of our product.\n\n - Prototype and test. You’ll create prototypes and conduct usability testing to refine designs based on user feedback.\n\n - Establish design guidelines. You’ll develop and maintain design guidelines to ensure product consistency across all platforms.\n\n\n\nWHAT WE’RE LOOKING FOR\n\n - 8+ years of experience in product design\n\n - Strong portfolio of design projects, ideally with consumer-facing applications\n\n - Proficiency in prototyping tools (e.g., Figma, Sketch, Adobe XD)\n\n - Excellent communication skills (written, verbal, and presentation)\n\n - Ability to work effectively in a fast-paced environment\n\n - An entrepreneurial mindset with the ability to bring an idea or vision to life.\n\n - A passion for the blockchain, decentralized finance, \u0026 freedom of speech.\n\n - (Plus) Experience designing for web and mobile platforms in the fintech or blockchain space\n\n - Understanding of financial markets, trading, and DeFi is a nice to have. Willingness to learn about them is a must.\n\n\n\nBENEFITS\n\n - Competitive salary \u0026 equity\n\n - Unlimited PTO\n\n - Full Health, Vision, \u0026 Dental coverage\n\n - 401k match\n\n - Hardware setup — new MacBook Pro, big display, \u0026 accessories",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
